title: For Sale/Trade:  PRICE DROP! HOLD OUT ON PYTHONS AND COLTS A LITTLE LONGER!!
postcontent: Hey just giving shooters a heads up on Colts, especially Pythons. Just wait it out a bit longer if your looking to get one of these fine guns because the market is about to drop big time later this year. Unfortunately a lot of investors got into them for investments only which drove up the prices. This caused shooter like myself not to be able afford them because they went from $800-$1500 guns to now $2,000-$4,000 guns depending on which version you had. These puppies are made to be shot and not tossed back and forth between investors. Pythons are still very common online and offline, but thanks to investors who bought them at a $1000 to sell for $1500 and so on till now, investors are peaking. Investors are now stuck trying to sell a blued python for $2000+ and they aren't moving. Keep the waiting because if you go to the shows like I do and go online a lot you see they aren't moving like they use to. Hell some people are trying to get a MKIII Troopers which is a $500-600 gun all day for over $1000. These guns weren't built smooth and are a poor mans Python. My Smith 19 and Ruger with outlast troopers all day long and are much smoother to shoot. With this sluggish economy and Obamacare sticking it to people, no one is going to drop $2000 on a python.  So keep holding out and watch the prices drop! This isn't anything different then when investors destroyed the Muscle Car market and the Comic book market. In the 90's certain comics sky rocketed and were valued in the hundreds and thousands of dollars, today you cant give them away, Those same comics can be bought online at Ebay for $5. SO HOLD OUT BECAUSE WHEN THE INVESTORS LEAVE THE PRICES WILL DROP!! I hope a lot of you investors take a huge hit!

title: For Sale:  Model 1895 Nagant revolver with ammunition
location: Santa Fe, NM, New Mexico, United States
postcontent:
Vintage 1933 Nagant Model 1895 Revolver. Made when Stalin was just consolidating power, and when Hitler was barely on anyone's radar screen.This is  an early one dated 1933 with the tiny CAI St. Albans import mark only on the barrel. Grips are a nice dark reddish brown color and not the current crop of orange ones. It is matching and the action on this one is smoother than most of the Pre-World War II Nagants I have owned. SA trigger pull is a joy, and the DA pull is quite manageable even before using the famous "bullet trick" to lighten it. I bought this one from a local collector, so it doesn't have one of the holsters that the later imports come with. I do have a leather lanyard for it, so that will be included as well. Since it doesn't have a holster, I thought I might add something you would actually use. I have 2 boxes of older Fiocchi ammo for it, plus 26 rounds of current PPU that is not pictured. I like this older Fiocchi ammo better than the current crop because it is loaded closer to the original power of the original surplus ammunition. This was made before the lawyers got to Fiocchi. So that's a total of 126 rounds of ammunition.  After you shoot it, save the box, because if you look again, they misspelled "Nagant" as "Naganat" lol. The PPU ammo is just some that I had left over so I may as well send it along so you can have plenty of ammo to play with the revolver. 

These shoot a unique and very cool round, the 7.62x38R or 7.62 Russian. However it also will shoot plain old .32 S&W, and it really likes .32 H&R Magnum, which fits it nicely. SO ammo is not a problem. All three are sold in most gun shops. The .32 H&R is a cool little self defense round by the way, especially with some of the hot rounds out there.

Contact me through Armslist and we can arrange to meet here in Santa Fe.

Thanks for reading my ad. Doby Pilgrim Santa Fe

title: For Sale:  Ruger Blackhawk .177 single shot break-barrel action pellet air rifle combination
postcontent:
Ruger Blackhawk .177 single shot break-barrel action pellet air rifle combination.  Satin black metal finish with black synthetic stock.  Fiber optic fixed front and adjustable rear "iron" sights.  4X fixed focus telescopic sight, parallax currently adjusted to approximately 5 yards for indoor winter shooting.  Telescopic sight attaches to grooved receiver with included rings.  Stock modified by installation of sling mounts, swivels and nylon sling.

Acquired about Mar 2012, approximately 1000 pellets fired since, so it is well broken in at this point.  No BBs have ever been near this rifle, let alone fired through it.  The .177 pellets it likes include:  Beeman 7.7 gr coated wadcutters; Crosman 7.4 grain competition and 7.9 grain premium wadcutters; Crosman 10.5 gr premier ultra magnum domes; JBS 13.4 gr match diabolo exact monster domes; and RWS 7.0 gr basics wadcutters.  As would any other self-respecting air rifle, it despises Daisy 7.2,3,4,5,? wadcutters.  I have used it to retrain in rifle marksmanship after a break of several decades.  I am looking to part with it now as I have since acquired and use as my principal air rifle a Benjamin Trail gas piston air rifle, have limited long gun storage space, and wish to use the space I have available for firearms.  Otherwise, I would keep and continue occasionally to shoot this rifle.

For image and formal description, see http://www.umarexusa.com/Ruger-Blackhawk-Air-Rifle.html

I shall included with the combo at no additional charge the sling and mountings previously mentioned and a 500 pellet tin of Beeman 7.7 gr coated wadcutters.  Further, I am willing to provide an Allen 46" padded nylon scoped rifle case for an additional $15 or a Plano 52" hard scoped rifle case for an additional $35.

You must be over 18 and have a photo ID with proof of age to buy this package.  If you are buying with intent to provide it to a person under 18, please make yourself fully aware of your responsibility to provide supervision to your intended recipient under Massachusetts law.
